com.engine.data

Class Catalog<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.engine.data.Catalog<E>

  • public class Catalog<E>
extends java.lang.Object

    Catalog

    A catalog is a graphical representation of a list of items. Each item is displayed on a background in the form of tiles. Catalog uses generics to allow a catalog of any data type.

    Catalog Components

    • A catalog contains different pages, CatalogPage.
    • Each page contains a maximum of 16 items, CatalogItem.
    • The layout and organization of the tiles is handled automatically.
    • A catalog contains next and previous page buttons by default.
    • A catalog contains a search box to search through it by keyword.

    NOTE: All components of a catalog can be customized. It will work without setting any custom images, etc. But a custom background, buttons, search box, etc. can be used.
    Author:
    Ryan Hochmuth
